>>64559032
>Yeah, I have a low tolerance and I took edibles
Ah, I see. Yeah, that's how people get got their first few times.

>What's wrong with edibles for noobs?
Edibles may seem like a great time -- get high without smoking or smelling weed -- but they're very hard to dose correctly, as most people metabolize THC through the gut/liver differently than through the lungs. What a 5mg edible is to me may be 50mg to you. Additionally, an edible high takes a few hours to kick in (as opposed to smoked/vaped flower, which is much quicker), so rookies will take EVEN MORE edibles in the time they're digesting the first one because they think it's not working. These types end up too stoned and hating weed forever usually. Edible highs, even at the right dose, are really different from a flower high, too.

Oh yeah. Weed can be a euphoric drug too. What most people find after getting high is an intense internal euphoria followed by a strong mood lift. Made even more powerful if you focus on those feelings and meditate on them while you're high. Everything feels better.

I prefer marijuana. MDMA is really fun, but you can only safely do it once every three months. Marijuana has a different method of action and can be used more frequently. Just too much if you don't know what you're getting into.
